The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD

 (Landmark, Rs 1,050) The two-disc bonanza chronicles the 

 rise of the British metal band. There are three concerts 

 featured, including 1983?s Live At Dortmund that 

 sees the group in top form. Home video footage and a 90-minute 

 documentary add to the treat. 

 THE SHOWCASE

 (Artisana, 11 am to 7 pm, from June 15) Crafts Council 

 of West Bengal presents this exhibition of T-shirts embellished 

 with traditional embroidery and paintings ? the kalighat 

 pata and Madhubani styles to kantha, zardozi, 

 ari, batik, block print and beadwork. 

 THE DISPLAY

 (Seagull 

 Arts amp; Media Resource Centre, 2 pm to 7 pm, June 18) The 

 French Association in collaboration with Seagull hosts this 

 display of photographs on sleepers. The work represents the 

 mental process behind the making of a photograph, and experiments 

 with different perspectives. 




